plot: Toby loses his memory due to a drug being introduced to his system. Soon afterwards, Toby finds himself implicated in a armed kidnapping.

Responding to the report of a strange, possibly armed man, Michelle finds Toby, with no memory of the previous ten hours and a bullet having been fired from his gun. Tests reveal he'd been slipped a drug to bend his will and erase his memory. Tracing his missing hours leads to a dead man tied to a chair, whom Toby helped to abduct. Did Toby kill the unarmed, defenseless man? Toby, above all, wants to know.—statmanjeff
